id":"1ae21454-b45d-47e9-a008-4e4828fc8cd8"}],"recipe_instructions":[{"id":"a6a0364a-5150-4bb6-b38e-b08b12d28ed2","title":"","summary":"","text":"Melt the butter in a medium saucepan. Once melted, whisk in the brown sugar. Bring to a boil over high heat and cook 1 minute. Remove from the heat and transfer to a bowl. Whisk in the vanilla. Add the almond flour and salt mixing until combined. Let cool 5 minutes, then stir in the egg white. Let the dough sit 10 minutes to thicken. ","ingredient_references":[]},{"id":"f4fcb114-d1f9-47a9-97c7-1463e5e7c0df","title":"","summary":"","text":"Position racks in the upper and lower thirds of the oven. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.","ingredient_references":[]},{"id":"50d6e412-743e-4aa8-ab95-9b59b5d3bbec","title":"","summary":"","text":"If you can roll the dough into balls, add 1 tablespoons water to thin. The dough should be thiner and look like my photo above. ","ingredient_references":[]},{"id":"8b421210-5c78-4ad6-86fd-8af2240ce030","title":"","summary":"","text":"Drop 1 teaspoons size amounts of dough on prepared baking sheet, placing each 3 inches apart. Bake for 7-9 minutes until golden brown around the edges. The butter will be bubbling up around the cookies, this is OK. Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cook completely. ","ingredient_references":[]},{"id":"2c976cc6-fb67-4c13-b856-5ea281085819","title":"","summary":"","text":"To make the filling. Combine chocolate and cream microwave-safe bowl and microwave, stirring every 45 seconds, until melted. Stir in the vanilla and coffee powder. Let cool 10 minutes, until slightly thickened and spreadable. ","ingredient_references":[]},{"id":"1503aa9a-58ef-45ff-9a36-94edc0e571e7","title":"","summary":"","text":"Sandwich each cookie with the chocolate filling or melted milk chocolate. Store cookies in an airtight container for up to 4 days.","ingredient_references":[]}],"nutritio